<subSubSection id="81F2A6BB1C7ABD0BFF44476F1596F8BA" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C957F5301C7ABD0BFF44476F1596F8BA" blockId="2.[151,1436,1792,2036]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7ABD0BFF44476F162AF8C0" bold="true" box="[199,321,1792,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A 
<taxonomicName id="0EE88EB31C7ABD0BFEE7476D16AEF8C0" box="[356,453,1794,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Calopterygidae" genus="Matrona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7ABD0BFEE7476D16AEF8C0" box="[356,453,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Matrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with reddish-brown wings, lacking any milky coloured reticulation at the wing bases of the male; apical 
<number id="7F20E7171C7ABD0BFE34474816AAF8E6" box="[439,449,1831,1855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="7F20E7171C7ABD0BFE4F474816B1F8E6" box="[460,474,1831,1855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="3.0">3</number>
rd of male fore wing subhyaline. Posclypeus metallic green. Ventral side of the apical segments of abdomen a conspicuous pale olive yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
