<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7ABD0BFDBA471F151DF851" box="[569,630,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Head</emphasis>
: Labium olive yellow, the lateral lobes black at tips. Labrum black with an olive yellow median band, narrowed in the middle; in older specimens the yellow colour reduced to two separate spots. Base of mandibles largely yellow. Anteclypeus black with an obscure yellow spot in the middle. Postclypeus shining metallic green. Frons and upper surface of head black with obscure metallic green sheen. Genae black. Antennae dark, with a yellowish stripe on pedicel. 
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7BBD0AFCAB476214F1F8FC" box="[808,922,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Prothorax</emphasis>
dark metallic green. 
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7BBD0AFB0E47621394F8FC" box="[1165,1279,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Synthorax</emphasis>
dark metallic green. Pale yellow portions are restricted to the level anterior to stigma and around metepimeron (
<figureCitation id="51D3E9B51C7BBD0AFB72475E125CF890" box="[1265,1335,1841,1865]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[234,1309,228,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1399,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 3) habitus of paratype male (right hind wing incomplete at base)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203455/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="7F20E7171C7BBD0AFAA4475E125CF890" box="[1319,1335,1841,1865]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Underside of synthorax largely pale yellow. 
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7BBD0AFDBC4739151FF8B4" box="[575,628,1878,1901]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Legs</emphasis>
: Coxae pale yellow with black markings on pro- and mesothoracic legs. Femora black with flexor surface partly pale in younger specimens, more markedly so in meso- and metathoracic legs. Tibiae black; meso- and metathoracic tibiae moderately curved (
<figureCitation id="51D3E9B51C7BBD0AFC2947F21485F86C" box="[938,1006,1949,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[234,1309,228,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1399,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 3) habitus of paratype male (right hind wing incomplete at base)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203455/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="7F20E7171C7BBD0AFC5C47F21485F86C" box="[991,1006,1949,1973]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7BBD0AFB8647F11323F86C" box="[1029,1096,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="51D3E9B51C7BBD0AFBD947F213F6F86C" box="[1114,1181,1949,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1738,1761]" captionTargetBox="[309,1245,226,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[309,1277,193,1717]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 6. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 5) wings of paratype male; 6) wings of paratype female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203456/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="7F20E7171C7BBD0AFB0C47F213F6F86C" box="[1167,1181,1949,1973]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) largely brownish, the apical 
<number id="7F20E7171C7BBD0AFF6047AB1786F805" box="[227,237,1988,2012]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="7F20E7171C7BBD0AFF7B47AB166DF805" box="[248,262,1988,2012]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="3.0">3</number>
rd of fore wing subhyaline; in hind wing the apical part slightly more hyaline than base; this difference less marked than in fore wing. In hind wing lower half darker in middle section of wing. Venation dark violet red. Reticulation sparse for genus, best seen in number of intercalary veins and density of crossveins in the area defined by CuP and wing border (
<figureCitation id="51D3E9B51C7CBD0DFE3940B01696FF2E" box="[442,509,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1660,1683]" captionTargetBox="[184,1398,898,1659]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,829,1698]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 7. Matrona taoi sp. nov. paratype male; venation at hind wing base." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFE6D40B01696FF2E" box="[494,509,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) and in wing tip. Only 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFC8740B0145BFF2E" box="[772,816,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
, partly reticulated, crossveins in median space. Cubital space with 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFE97416B1631FEC5" box="[276,346,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="18.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="17.0">17–20</number>
crossveins in fore wing, 
<quantity id="0E1058D51C7CBD0DFDF0416B15BDFEC5" box="[627,726,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.699" metricValueMax="5.08" metricValueMin="4.318" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="18.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="17.0">17–20 in</quantity>
hind wing (in 
<typeStatus id="16534B921C7CBD0DFCFA416B14B0FEC5" box="[889,987,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFC61416B1495FEC5" box="[994,1022,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="20.0">20</number>
crossveins in all wings). Quadrangle with 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFF534148167DFEE6" box="[208,278,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="15.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="13.0">13–18</number>
crossveins in fore wing, 
<quantity id="0E1058D51C7CBD0DFDB7414815F3FEE6" box="[564,664,295,319]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" metricValueMax="5.08" metricValueMin="3.556" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="17.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="14.0">14–20 in</quantity>
hind wing (in 
<typeStatus id="16534B921C7CBD0DFCC3414814C9FEE6" box="[832,930,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFC29414814AEFEE6" box="[938,965,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="15.0">15</number>
– 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFC564148149BFEE6" box="[981,1008,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="13.0">13</number>
and 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFBAB4148132FFEE6" box="[1064,1092,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="18.0">18</number>
– 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFBD74148131BFEE6" box="[1108,1136,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="18.0">18</number>
, respectively). Antenodals (in first row) number 
<quantity id="0E1058D51C7CBD0DFE1741231692FEBD" box="[404,505,332,356]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1938" metricValueMax="1.3462" metricValueMin="1.0413999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="47.0" valueMax="53.0" valueMin="41.0">41–53 in</quantity>
fore wing and 
<quantity id="0E1058D51C7CBD0DFD2F41231479FEBD" box="[684,786,332,356]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0668" metricValueMax="1.2192" metricValueMin="0.9144" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="42.0" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="36.0">36–48 in</quantity>
hind wing (in 
<typeStatus id="16534B921C7CBD0DFC4341231349FEBD" box="[960,1058,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFBAF4123132CFEBD" box="[1068,1095,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="41.0">41</number>
– 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFBD54123131AFEBD" box="[1110,1137,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="41.0">41</number>
and 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFB2E412313A2FEBD" box="[1197,1225,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="38.0">38</number>
– 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFB5A4123139DFEBD" box="[1241,1270,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="36.0">36</number>
, respectively). Arculus (Arc) situated at the level of the fifth antenodal. Pterostigma absent in both wings. 
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7CBD0DFB1F411F126DFE51" box="[1180,1286,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Abdomen</emphasis>
metallic bluish-green dorsally and laterally; the lower half of side of S 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFC9C41FB1457FE75" box="[799,828,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="10.0">10</number>
yellow (
<figureCitation id="51D3E9B51C7CBD0DFC1E41FB148AFE75" box="[925,993,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[234,1309,228,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1399,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 3) habitus of paratype male (right hind wing incomplete at base)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203455/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFC5241FB148AFE75" box="[977,993,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ventral side of S 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFB2C41FB13D1FE75" box="[1199,1210,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="1.0">1</number>
-S 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFB5741FB1388FE75" box="[1236,1251,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="5.0">5</number>
blackish brown, S 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFF2541D817A0FE16" box="[166,203,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6-7</number>
obscurely pale yellow and S 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFD9141D81574FE16" box="[530,543,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="8.0">8</number>
-S 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFDB441D8153EFE16" box="[567,597,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="10.0">10</number>
conspicuous pale olive yellow (
<figureCitation id="51D3E9B51C7CBD0DFC4341D81363FE16" box="[960,1032,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[325,1265,196,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[297,1286,193,1947]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Matrona taoi sp. nov., damselflies photographed in the field in Xuan Son by Phan Quoc Toan on 15 December 2010. 1) male; 2) female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203454/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Figs 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFC7941D81363FE16" box="[1018,1032,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="1.3">1</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="51D3E9B51C7CBD0DFB9441D8134DFE16" box="[1047,1062,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[234,1309,228,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1399,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 3) habitus of paratype male (right hind wing incomplete at base)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203455/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">3</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7CBD0DFBBF41D71394FE09" box="[1084,1279,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Anal appendages</emphasis>
of the typical shape for the genus: cercus wholly black, bearing a row of small spines laterally; paraproct more than half of the length of cercus, black at tip, yellow laterally and ventrally.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9D97A5B81C7BBD0AFF1446A51337F939" box="[151,1116,1738,1761]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203456/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" targetBox="[309,1245,226,1681]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="C957F5301C7BBD0AFF1446A51337F939" blockId="3.[151,1116,1738,1761]" box="[151,1116,1738,1761]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7BBD0AFF1446A51652F939" bold="true" box="[151,313,1738,1761]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">FIGURES 5–6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="0EE88EB31C7BBD0AFEC346A416ADF939" box="[320,454,1739,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Calopterygidae" genus="Matrona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7BBD0AFEC346A416ADF939" box="[320,454,1739,1760]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Matrona taoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7BBD0AFE4F46A41553F938" bold="true" box="[460,568,1738,1761]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E0AF94591C7BBD0AFE4F46A41577F939" box="[460,540,1739,1760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
5)
</emphasis>
wings of paratype male; 
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7BBD0AFCBA46A51425F938" bold="true" box="[825,846,1738,1761]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">6)</emphasis>
wings of paratype female.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="C957F5301C7CBD0DFF44424B12F7FDE5" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,825]" box="[199,1436,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7CBD0DFF44424B161DFDE5" bold="true" box="[199,374,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Measurements</emphasis>
(mm): 
<collectingCountry id="B1FFB5A01C7CBD0DFE4A424B156AFDE5" box="[457,513,548,572]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFDC5424B15E6FDE5" box="[582,653,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="40.0" valueMax="42.0" valueMin="38.0">38–42</number>
(in 
<typeStatus id="16534B921C7CBD0DFD3B424B1471FDE5" box="[696,794,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFCA2424B142BFDE5" box="[801,832,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="38.0">38</number>
); abdomen (incl. appendages) 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFB16424B13B0FDE5" box="[1173,1243,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="57.5" valueMax="61.0" valueMin="54.0">54–61</number>
(in 
<typeStatus id="16534B921C7CBD0DFA84424B1202FDE5" box="[1287,1385,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFAF3424B12FBFDE5" box="[1392,1424,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="54.0">54</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C957F5301C7CBD0DFF4442281348FCEE" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7CBD0DFF44422816BBFDB9" bold="true" box="[199,464,583,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Description of female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="51D3E9B51C7CBD0DFE6642281558FD86" box="[485,563,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[325,1265,196,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[297,1286,193,1947]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Matrona taoi sp. nov., damselflies photographed in the field in Xuan Son by Phan Quoc Toan on 15 December 2010. 1) male; 2) female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203454/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Figs 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFDA042281558FD86" box="[547,563,583,607]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.4">2</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="51D3E9B51C7CBD0DFDC742281538FD86" box="[580,595,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionTargetBox="[234,1309,228,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[187,1399,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 3) habitus of paratype male (right hind wing incomplete at base)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203455/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">4</figureCitation>
): Head and thorax coloured as in male. Wings (
<figureCitation id="51D3E9B51C7CBD0DFB1842281388FD86" box="[1179,1251,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1738,1761]" captionTargetBox="[309,1245,226,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[309,1277,193,1717]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 6. Matrona taoi sp. nov. 5) wings of paratype male; 6) wings of paratype female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203456/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFB5642281388FD86" box="[1237,1251,583,607]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) reddish-brown throughout, an obscure darker band in the apical third of hind wing, the darker colour extending basad along wing border. Venation reddish brown to pale brown. Reticulation as sparse as in male. Median space of fore wing with 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFF1442DB17AAFD15" box="[151,193,692,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
crossveins; 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFED142DB1617FD15" box="[338,380,692,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
crossveins in hind wing. Cubital space with 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFC0842DB14BBFD15" box="[907,976,692,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="20.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="18.0">18–23</number>
crossveins in fore wing, 
<quantity id="0E1058D51C7CBD0DFB7942DB120AFD15" box="[1274,1377,692,716]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.207" metricValueMax="5.842" metricValueMin="4.572" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="20.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="18.0">18–23 in</quantity>
hind wing. Quadrangle with 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFE2742B81681FD36" box="[420,490,727,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="16.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="12.0">12–20</number>
crossveins in fore wing, 
<quantity id="0E1058D51C7CBD0DFC8842B81404FD36" box="[779,879,727,751]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" metricValueMax="4.826" metricValueMin="3.81" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="17.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="15.0">15–19 in</quantity>
hind wing. Antenodals (in the first row) number 
<quantity id="0E1058D51C7CBD0DFF1442931790FCCD" box="[151,251,764,788]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2573" metricValueMax="1.3716" metricValueMin="1.143" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="49.5" valueMax="54.0" valueMin="45.0">45–54 in</quantity>
fore wing and 
<quantity id="0E1058D51C7CBD0DFE2942931565FCCD" box="[426,526,764,788]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1303" metricValueMax="1.2192" metricValueMin="1.0413999999999999" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="44.5" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="41.0">41–48 in</quantity>
hind wing. Pseudopterostigma yellowish cream, short, covering 
<number id="7F20E7171C7CBD0DFB7242931271FCCD" box="[1265,1306,764,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6–9</number>
underlying cells. Abdomen dark reddish brown, the apical segments obscurely pale laterally.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9D97A5B81C7CBD0DFF14461314C5F94B" box="[151,942,1660,1683]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" targetBox="[184,1398,898,1659]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="C957F5301C7CBD0DFF14461314C5F94B" blockId="4.[151,942,1660,1683]" box="[151,942,1660,1683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7CBD0DFF1446131678F94B" bold="true" box="[151,275,1660,1683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">FIGURE 7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="0EE88EB31C7CBD0DFE9A461116F5F94A" box="[281,414,1662,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Calopterygidae" genus="Matrona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7CBD0DFE9A461116F5F94A" box="[281,414,1662,1683]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Matrona taoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E0AF94591C7CBD0DFE274612169EF94B" box="[420,501,1661,1682]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" rank="species">
<emphasis id="FB9C29221C7CBD0DFE274612169EF94B" bold="true" box="[420,501,1661,1682]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
paratype male; venation at hind wing base.
